      "Suddenly, Loki is captured in a portal, leaving a mysterious address card, which leads Thor to Bleecker Street. There, he finds Doctor Strange, who insists on knowing why Loki has returned to Earth knowing how dangerous it is. Thor explains that they are simply trying to find Odin and will immediately leave as soon as they find him. Strange reveals that he knows Odin's whereabouts, but the latter had insisted on preventing him from being disturbed. However, he still sends Thor and Loki back with their father.",
      "Thor and Loki find Odin, having already freed himself from Loki's spell, but he is dejected and dying. In her last moments, Odin makes a confession: Hela, the Goddess of Death, sister of Thor and Loki that they never knew, will be released from prison once he dies. She is much more powerful than her brothers and will become stronger when she returns to Asgard. Odin tells his children that he loves them for the last time, before transforming into energy and dying.",
