      "Meanwhile, Thor falls on the planet Sakaar. He notices various portals and wormholes discarding trash to the surface, before continuing on his way. Thor is confronted by hostile gatherers, whom he manages to fight without the Mjolnir until one of them uses an electrified network to capture him. The scavengers proceed to hit Thor until a spaceship lands near them. From there comes a drunk woman, who claims that Thor will come with her. The woman kills the scavengers with her ship's weapons, apparently rescuing Thor. Unfortunately, she ends up throwing a small disc in his neck, which allows him to electrocute him with the press of a button to make him unconscious. She takes the God of Thunder on her ship with the Grand Master.",
      "In Asgard, the Asgardian army, led by Hogun, has gathered to prevent Hela from entering the kingdom. After refusing to kneel before her new queen, Hela impales the soldiers and ships alike with her endless arsenal of swords and spears, ending even with Hogun. She assumes the throne and destroys the royal mural above him, revealing the secret that Odin tried to hide. Hela revealed herself to be Odin's most powerful weapon in her efforts to create the powerful Asgardian empire, and when her ambition surpassed Odin's, she ended up imprisoned.",
