      "The champion is revealed as Hulk. Thor, delighted to see his former teammate, tries to talk and negotiate with him, but makes the mistake of calling him 'Banner'. Thor tries to lull him like Natalia Romanoff used to do, but it doesn't work. Hulk dominates him during the battle and is about to kill him, but Thor witnesses a vision of his father, causing an increase in his powers. As the fight continues, Thor takes the lead by firing his thunder abilities, but the Grandmaster, unwilling to see Hulk lose, cheats and «fixes» the fight by activating the disc on Thor's neck, immobilizing him, and allowing Hulk defeat him.",
      "Thor wakes up in a luxurious accommodation with Hulk. The latter refuses to return to Earth because he believes that everyone hates him there and, therefore, will not leave Sakaar. Thor also cannot escape for the safety of the place, but upon discovering that Hulk and Brunnhilde are training partners, he decides to use this in his favor for Hulk to call her and thus deceive her in order to steal the control device from her neck. The plan was successful, and Thor escapes while being chased by Hulk, who wants his «friend» to stay.",
      "Thor tries to reach the Quinjet that transported Hulk to Sakaar, but the latter arrives and ends up damaging the ship. Thor accidentally activates a Romanoff recording trying to convince Hulk to turn the Quinjet, causing Hulk to calm down and return to being Bruce Banner. Banner has been transformed from Hulk since Sokovia and, as a result, Hulk had taken control of his body. Because of this, Banner does not remember anything that has happened during the past two years, and fears that if he becomes Hulk again, he may not return to his human form.",
      "The Grand Master orders Brunnhilde and Loki to track Thor for capturing his champion. Brunnhilde finds him, and agrees to help the duo, as he knocked out Loki after he made her see a vision of herself and her sisters who fell at the hands of Hela millennia ago, where she was the only survivor of the massacre, and is willing to die facing his past. Loki, not wanting to continue staying in Sakaar, tells Thor that he has the Grand Master's security codes that give him control over his systems. Heimdall also communicates with Thor and advises him to go through a portal called Devil's Butt to escape and get to Asgard as soon as possible. Later, Brunnhilde releases Korg and Miek so they can begin the slave revolution as a distraction so they can steal the Grand Master's personal ship, which is strong enough to cross the Devil's Butt.",
      "Back in Asgard, Skurge has gathered civilians to demand the location of the stolen sword. As nobody speaks, Hela asks him to execute a randomly chosen woman, although Skurge seems to feel uncomfortable with this. Just before he can do it, a civilian agrees to tell Hela what he wants if he promises to let the woman live.",
      "Loki inevitably betrays the team as they escape, but Thor had already silently placed one of the control discs on his back, leaving him motionless on the ground. Thor tells his brother that he expected more from him, remarking that part of life is to mature instead of going around, before boarding the Grand Master's Commodore, and escaping with his friends. Later, Loki is found by Korg and a group of slaves, who turn off the control device. Loki assumes the leadership of the revolution and steals a large ship with them, the Statesman.",
      "Thor, Brunnhilde and Banner arrive in Asgard. Hela begins an assault on the fortress where Heimdall is hiding the Asgardian civilians, but Thor calls her back to the throne room to fight. Banner and Brunnhilde fight to help civilians escape through the Bifrost, but they are cornered by the army of Hela and Fenris. Seeing the danger of the situation, Banner decides to jump off the ship and transforms into the Hulk to confront Fenris, while Loki arrives with Korg and his allies to face the enemy army. Thor is dominated by Hela, who hits him in the face and cuts his right eye. Once again, Thor has a vision of his father, who tells him that Asgard is not a place, it is a town, and his powers are superior to those of Odin.",
      "Recovering his strength, Thor manages to awaken his powers against Hela and then fights against his army, however, he realizes that he is still too powerful for him. Thor and Loki agree that as long as Asgard exists, she will become more powerful. Therefore, Thor concludes that they must provoke Ragnarök, since the prophecy indicated that Asgard should fall and in this way his people will be able to survive from Hela. Thor and Brunnhilde gain time confronting Hela while Loki returns to the Chamber of Odin for the Crown of Surtur, noticing the Teseract on the road, stealthily stealing it. Later, Loki places the crown on the Eternal Flame, allowing Surtur to be reborn.",
      "The now more powerful Surtur begins to devastate Asgard and even Hela cannot stop him. She tries to prevent the stateswoman where the Asgardians were evacuated from escaping, but Skurge betrays her and kills the rest of her soldiers before she murders him. Thor soon takes Hela from the bridge. On the other hand, Hulk ends Fenris, and attacks Surtur, but Thor stops him. Reluctantly, Hulk takes Thor and Brunnhilde aboard the Statesman, escaping away from Asgard. Hela suddenly emerges from the water and begins to impale Surtur, who kills her once and for all with his sword. In the act, Asgard is completely destroyed, killing Surtur and leaving behind only asteroids. Thor understands that the destruction of his home was inevitable, and that Asgard still exists, but in his people.",
      "Thor begins to wear an eye patch, similar to his father's. He thanks Loki for his return, and the two brothers finally reconcile. Thor then approaches his throne chair, while the surviving Asgardians stare at him. Thor becomes the new King of Asgard, with Loki, Hulk, Heimdall, Brunnhilde, Korg and Miek at his side. When asked where to go, Thor decides to establish his people on Earth.",
